A Vietnam War veteran has received a Purple Heart 45 years after being injured in the war.

James R. Below's truck was blown up by a landmine and he saved the life of a fellow soldier, but his bravery has never been recognised until now.

Yesterday he was presented with the military decoration during a special afternoon ceremony in the Law Library of the Winfield K. Denton Federal Building, in Evansville, Southwestern Indiana.

